# <%= name %>

React application with SSR and routing, generated by `@canonical/summon-application`.

## Running the app

The server scripts form a **2×3 matrix** — two modes (development vs preview)
across three targets (SPA, SSR on Bun, SSR on Node/Express):

|                   | `dev` — transform, HMR  | `preview` — compiled, production-faithful |
| ----------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| **SPA** (no SSR)  | `bun run dev`           | `bun run preview`                         |
| **SSR · Bun**     | `bun run dev:bun`       | `bun run preview:bun`                     |
| **SSR · Node**    | `bun run dev:express`   | `bun run preview:express`                 |

Naming rule: the bare name is the **SPA**; the `:bun` / `:express` suffix selects
the **SSR** runtime. `dev*` is the fast inner loop (Vite transforms source on the
fly, with HMR); `preview*` builds the client and runs a **compiled** renderer
over the built assets — the same shape that deploys. Use `dev:*` while building;
run `preview:*` to verify the production bundle before you deploy.

```bash
# Storybook
bun run storybook
```

## Adding routes

```bash
# Create a new domain
summon domain billing

# Add a route to a domain
summon route billing/invoices

# Create a layout wrapper
summon wrapper sidebar
```

## Structure

```
src/
├── client/         Client entry (hydration)
├── server/         SSR entry + dev servers
├── domains/        Feature domains (routes + pages)
├── lib/            Shared components
├── styles/         CSS
├── assets/         Imported assets (bundled by Vite)
└── routes.tsx      Root route map
public/             Static files served as-is (favicon, robots.txt)
```

> **Note:** this app ships both `src/assets/` (assets imported in code) and `public/`
> (files served by fixed URL). Keeping both by default is provisional — you may remove
> whichever your app doesn't use.
